addRecord

public void addRecord(java.lang.Object[] row)
               throws InvalidStructureException,
                      NotUniqueException,
                      OperationNotAllowedException
addRecord appends another row to the CRecordTable structure by constructing a CRecordTable.Record object to represent the row data passed in form the row parameter. However, if the row data passed in does not match in size to the number of columns, then a InvalidStructureException is thrown.
